Package gov.nih.nlm.meme.integrity

Provides all classes for the MEME integrity system.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
BinaryDataIntegrityCheck Generically represents a data driven integrity check that requires two pieces of information (in this case taken from ic_pair).
DataConstraint Generically represents an integrity check that takes a single Concept and validates some aspect of its content.
IntegrityCheck Generically represents an integrity check.
IntegrityVector Generically represents a vector of IntegrityChecks used by an application to validate content.
MergeInhibitor Generically represents an IntegrityCheck that takes two Concepts and determines whether or not merging them would create an illegal state.
MoveInhibitor Generically represents an IntegrityCheck that takes two Concepts and determines whether or not moving Atoms from one to the other would create an illegal state.
UnaryDataIntegrityCheck Generically represents a data driven integrity check that requires one additional piece of information (in this case taken from ic_single).
 

Class Summary
AbstractBinaryDataMergeInhibitor Abstract implementation of a MergeInhibitor that is also a BinaryDataIntegrityCheck.
AbstractDataConstraint Abstract implementation a DataConstraint.
AbstractMergeInhibitor Abstract implementation of a MergeInhibitor.
AbstractMoveInhibitor Abstract implementation of MoveInhibitor
AbstractUnaryDataMergeInhibitor Abstract implementation of a MergeInhibitor that is also a UnaryDataIntegrityCheck.
BinaryCheckData Used to track data values used by a BinaryDataIntegrityCheck.
DT_I10 Validates those Concepts that contain a current version MSH/MH where the same-code previous year MSH/MH is in a different Concept.
DT_I11 Validates those Concepts that contain an SFO/LFO relationship to a different Concept
DT_I12 Validates those Concepts that contain a releasable NON_HUMAN attribute without valid semantic type (as defined by nhsty).
DT_I13 Validates those Concepts that contain a current version MSH/PM (permuted term) without a current version same-code MSH/EN, EP, or MH.
DT_I14 Validates Concepts that contain a current version MSH/N1 without a current version same-code MSH/N1 or NM.
DT_I2 Validates those Concepts that contain at least one releasable Atom merged by the merge engine, indicated by an ENG-% Authority.
DT_I3 Validates those Concepts that contain at least one demoted Relationship.
DT_I3B Validates those Concepts which contain at least one demoted Relationship without a matching releasable MTH asserted Relationship.
DT_I4 Validates those Concepts that contain at least one Relationship with Authority like 'PIR%'.
DT_I5 Validates those Concepts that contain a releasable NON_HUMAN attribute.
DT_I6 Not implemented.
DT_I8 Superclass code for the various DT_I8* integrity checks.
DT_I8A Validates those Concepts that contain MSH "entry term" with D# code matching a MSH/MH in a different Concept with NO approved, releasable, RT, NT, BT, or non MTH asserted LK Relationship to that Concept.
DT_I8AXR Validates those Concept that contain MSH "entry term" with D# code matching a MSH/MH in a different Concept with an approved, releasable XR Relationship to that Concept which overrides any other valid relationships.
DT_I8B Validates those Concept that contain MSH "entry term" with Q# code matching a MSH/TQ in a different Concept with NO approved, releasable, RT, NT, BT, or non MTH asserted LK Relationship to that Concept.
DT_I8BXR Validates those concept that contain MSH "entry term" with Q# code matching a MSH/TQ in a different Concept with an approved, releasable XR Relationship to that Concept which overrides any other valid Relationships.
DT_I8C Validates those Concepts that contain MSH "entry term" with C# code matching a MSH/NM in a different Concept with NO approved (or unreviewed), releasable, RT, NT, BT, or non MTH asserted LK Relationship to that Concept.
DT_I8CXR Validates those Concepts that contain MSH "entry term" with C# code matching a MSH/NM in a different Concept with an approved, releasable XR Relationship to that Concept which overrides any other valid Relationships.
DT_I8XR Superclass for the various code DT_I8XR* integrity checks.
DT_I9 Validates those Concepts that contain a current version MSH "entry term" and the same approved, releasable Relationship to its MSH MH as another Concept which also has a current version MSH "entry term" with a matching code.

DT_PN2 Validates those Concepts which contain multiple releasable MTH/PN Atoms.

MGV_A1 Validates merges between two Concepts where both contain "released as approved" atoms.
MGV_A2 Validates merges between two Concepts where both are approved.
MGV_A3 Validates merges between two Concepts where both are unreviewed (status='R').
MGV_A4 Validates merges between two Concepts that were released previously with different CUIs.
MGV_ADHOC Validates merges between two Concepts where one contains a releasable, current version MDR Atom and the other has a chemical ConceptSemanticType.
MGV_B Validates merges between two Concepts that both contain releasable Atoms from the same Source and that Source is listed in ic_single.
MGV_B2 Validates merges between two Concepts where both contain releasable Atoms from the same Source and the Source is in ic_single.
MGV_C Validates merges between two Concepts where both contain releasable current version MSH Atoms.
MGV_D Validates merges between two Concepts that contain different releasable Relationships to the same latest version MSH/MH.
MGV_E Validates merging between two Concepts.
MGV_F Validates merging between two Concepts.
MGV_G Validates merges between two Concepts where one contains a previous version MSH/MH Atom and the other contains a releasable, latest version MSH Atom and their Codes are different.
MGV_H1 Validates merges between two Concepts where both contain releasable current version MSH Atoms with different Codes, specifically (D-D, Q-Q, D-Q, Q-D).
MGV_H2 Validates merges between two Concepts where both contain releasable current version MSH Atoms with different Codes, specifically (D-C, C-C).
MGV_I Validates merges between two Concepts that both contain releasable Atoms from the same Source but different Codes and that Source is listed in ic_single.
MGV_J Validates merges between two Concepts that contain releasable Atoms across Sources (usually previous and update versions of same source) but different Codes where these Sources are listed in ic_pair.
MGV_K Validates merges between merging two Concepts in such a way to produce an MGV_J violation, unless the merge will not increase the distinct Code count in the target Concept.
MGV_L Validates merges between Concepts in which one contains one object (STY,source,termgroup) and the other contains an incompatible object as listed in ic_pair.
MGV_M Validates merges between two Concepts that contain releasable "NEC" Atoms with different Sources.
MGV_MM Validates merges between Concepts where both contain releasable MTH/MM Atoms.
MGV_MM1 Not implemented.
MGV_MM1B Not implemented.
MGV_MM2 Not implemented.
MGV_MUI Validate merges between two Concepts where both contain current version MSH Atoms with different MUIs.
MGV_PN Validates merges between Concepts where both contain releasable MTH/PN Atoms.
MGV_RXCUI Validate merges between two Concepts with different RXCUIs.
MGV_STY Validates merges between two Concepts where both contain releasable semantic types from the same Source and the Source is in ic_single.
MVS_A Validates splits where the source Concept contains atoms with the same last released cui values.
MVS_MM2 Not implemented.
